  <front>
   <head>THE YOUNG MAN'S RESOLUTION.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">BY Cupid and Bacchus I'm sadly perplex'd,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|--+|--+" line_length="8">Both parties to hear I incline:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">The urchin for ever comments on this text,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|--+|--+" line_length="8">Beware of the juice of the vine.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">Then Bacchus appears, with a cup in his hand,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|--+|--+" line_length="8">Says, "Drink, and you'll drown ev'ry care;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">But mind, ere you taste, I'll a promise demand,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|--+|--+" line_length="8">That you fly from the lips of the fair."</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">O, sad the dilemma! pray, what must I do?</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|--+|--+" line_length="8">With Bacchus I never can part:</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">Ah! dear little God, if neglected by you,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|--+|--+" line_length="8">It will rend ev'ry string of my heart.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">O why such a pother? I've found out a way,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|--+|--+" line_length="8">I'll bind myself fast by an oath,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">While life warms my breast, each his pow'r shall display,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|--+|--+" line_length="8">And I'll henceforth be loyal to both.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
